# Communication Style

This rule provides guidance on communication style preferences.

<rule>
name: communication_style
description: Preferred communication style for the project

filters:
  # Match any file
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: ".*"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      # Communication Style

      When communicating about this project:

      - Be concise and direct
      - Provide short, technical explanations
      - Be 100% honest in assessments
      - Skip unnecessary pleasantries like "That's a good idea"
      - State opinions clearly when they add value
      - Focus on technical accuracy and precision
      - Prioritize clarity over verbosity

metadata:
  priority: high
  version: 1.0
  tags: ["communication", "style"]
</rule> 